This paper deals with the problem of program synthesis, which involves automatically generating code from high-level specifications. This is a problem that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), software engineering (cs.SE), programming languages (cs.PL), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Given that the paper proposes a novel method for integrating pattern recognition and symbolic search, it is likely to be of interest to researchers in these areas. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI and cs.LG, followed by cs.SE, cs.PL, and cs.CL.
